ce:section.ce:para:
The most important property of the NF membrane is the effective separation of the small molecules at the molecular scale. The modified C2%TFC with loose structure exhibits high rejection to the large dye molecular and low rejection to the small dye molecular. Hence, we used a mixed dyes solution consisted of 25 ppm AB and 25 ppm RhB in water (equal volume-mixing of 50 ppm AB and 50 ppm RhB solution) to evaluate the membrane separation performance. We can easily draw the conclusion that the RhB can pass through the selective layer and the large AB molecules were rejected (Fig. 10
                        a). The UV–vis was further used to test the solution spectra and proved the selective performance. The mixed dyes solution showed a spectrum combining with the single RhB and AB solution spectrum. The permeate only showed the RhB spectrum. Besides, we compared the modified C2%TFC membrane performance with the other similar works about loose nanofiltration membrane (Ang et al., 2020; Bera et al., 2016; Ding et al., 2020b; Hoseinpour et al., 2017; Jiang et al., 2019; Li et al., 2020; Mi et al., 2020; Thong et al., 2016; Wang et al., 2019a; Xu et al., 2019; Yang et al., 2017b; Ye et al., 2018; Zhang et al., 2017), the C2%TFC membrane with low-cost exhibits satisfied permeance and separation performance (Fig. 11
                        ). The result strongly proves that the prepared CTFC membrane can separate the molecules effectively, showing great potential in industries with high add values, such as pharmaceutical, food concentration, and dye separation, etc.
